post_text:
Good Tuesday afternoon everyone!

Here is some information on this week's volleyball matches.

Tonight @ Freeman

Parents, students, siblings, etc below grade 9 and above grade 12 (college, adult) need to have a voucher to enter the volleyball match on Tuesday at Freeman. Each uniformed athlete in grades 7-12 (since we play jh and hs volleyball that night) will receive 4 vouchers. There is no admission price for the game. High school students will just have to announce to the gate keeper that they are an I-W student, so they will not need a voucher.

Thursday @ Canton

Restrictions: Masks are required upon entrance and for the duration. Social distancing is recommended. All fans will enter through our temperature checkpoint upon entry.
Admission Prices: $2 per person

Invitations: You will need an invitation to receive entrance to this match. That invite is attached to this e-mail. Four invites per rostered player, essential team personnel, and coach. The spectators presenting the invitation will still need to pay.

Streaming: http://chawks.liveticket.tv/

Thank you and GO EAGLES!!!

Good Thursday afternoon!

It seems like it has been far too long since we have been able to host an event. At this point we are not restricting access to the games. Masks are highly encouraged/recommended for all indoor and outdoor activities. Honestly, if we want to see our activity seasons played in their entirety and we want to see in-person instruction continue with as few interruptions as possible, we will need everyone's help. Spectators that are in attendance are asked to socially distance from non-family members.

Tonight's volleyball game will be broadcast live on the Irene-Wakonda High School Youtube page. Tomorrow night's football game will not be broadcast.

Senior Night will be Friday, August 28th for football and cheer. Volleyball and cross country will have their Senior Night on Tuesday, September 15th.

Thank you!

It’s Back!!!! The free meals(breakfast/lunch) for students will start again on Wednesday, June 3rd and be available thru June 30th. The meals will only be pick-up and has two site options for pick-up:

1. Wakonda Elementary: Pick-up location has changed to the double glass doors for the kitchen entrance which is located in the parking lot by the little league field at the school.
2. Irene Lutheran Church parking lot: Due to current road construction, the pick-up location at this time will be in the Lutheran Church parking lot.

Meals will be available Monday – Thursday(Friday’s meals will be included in Thursday’s pick-up). Pick-up times will be the following:

1. Wakonda Elementary kitchen entrance: 11:00 – 12:00.
2. Irene Lutheran Church parking lot: 11:30 – 12:30.

Please email Pam Rudd at pam.rudd@k12.sd.us or call her at 605-263-3359 to sign-up for the meals.

Have a great day,
David Hutchison, Superintendent
Irene-Wakonda School District
605-263-3311

Dear JH/HS Parents,

Congratulations, you have made it to the end of the school year!!! I would like to offer a huge THANK YOU to you for all the supports you have given our students and teachers throughout this fourth quarter. THANK YOU!!!!

The school will be open for students to check in their textbooks, laptops, and any other items on Monday, May 18th and Tuesday, May 19th, from 9:00AM - 1:00PM. Students on bus routes may have their materials picked up by their bus driver on Monday. If you wish to have the bus driver pick up your students materials, you will need to contact the bus driver in advance.

Thank you,
Bruce Bailey

The 2020 Commencement Ceremony will be held on Saturday, June 13th at the football with an 11:00AM start time. At this time, we are planning to have as close to a complete ceremony as possible. In the case that a change in venue is necessary, those changes to the venue will be communicated as soon as possible.

Alternatives for date, time, and location have also been discussed. An alternative date/time has been set for Sunday, June 14th at 1:00PM. The alternative location would be the park east of the high school.

To support the need for safe social distancing, the district asks that spectators be limited to immediate family and grandparents.

Good Thursday evening everyone
,
On Monday, April 6th Governor Noem announced all schools will remain closed for the remainder of the school year. It was also stated that schools will continue to educate students with the flex/alternate teaching/learning methods until the end of their school year. The school year will end on Friday, May 15th for the Irene-Wakonda School District. Also, Irene-Wakonda Schools is offering free lunches/breakfast for all students through the end of the school year. I encourage parents to sign their students up for these meals. Please go to www.irene-wakonda.k12.sd.us for additional pertinent information.
https://tinyurl.com/vwpy9uu

Stay safe and have a great Easter,
Superintendent Hutchison

post_text:
The Depot of Irene

As most of you know, the schools are closed next week to try and minimize the spread of the Coronavirus. We at The Depot are concerned about our community and the children in it; and are prepared to help in any way we can.
So, we want to do our part and offer breakfast and lunch to any child who otherwise would not get it because of the school closure.

The Depot will have an egg & cheese breakfast sandwich and bag lunch available for any child who needs it from 7-10am M-F next week.

Please share and let others know. If you know me, you know that children and animals will NEVER go hungry on my watch.
Thanks!

Elise & Tom Strasmann

post_text:
Press Release- For Immediate Release

At the request of Governor Noem, the remainder of the SDHSAA Class B Girls Basketball tournament is postponed. In addition, all SDHSAA state basketball tournaments for next weekend, along with the Visual Arts competition, are also postponed. The Student Council Convention, all Region music contests, and All-State Band scheduled for later this month are cancelled.

This is a difficult decision and comes amid constant conversation and information sharing between the SDHSAA, the Governor’s Office, and the Department of Health. We will evaluate the future of the postponed events in concert with those same entities. The safety of everyone involved is our foremost concern, followed by exploring all options to provide the student-athlete with the opportunity to finish their season.

We thank everyone for their patience and understanding in a very difficult time, and we apologize for any inconvenience that this may cause.

Dan Swartos, SDHSAA Executive Director

The girls basketball team will be traveling to Huron to play Langford on Thursday, March 5th in the SoDak16. The winner will advance to the State Tournament in Spearfish. Tipoff is scheduled for 6:00PM at the Huron Arena.

School will be dismissed at 12:30(JH/HS) and 12:45(Elem) on Thursday, March 5th to allow our bus drivers to run their routes and prepare for the trip to Huron. There will be a pep rally at 12:05.

There will be a fan bus, occupancy is 45 people with seats being filled on a first come basis. Please contact Pam Erickson at 605-263-3311 to reserve your seat(s). The fan bus is open to any students grades 7 - 12, elementary students accompanied by a parent/adult, as well as any adult. The school is providing the fan bus at no cost to any passengers. The fan bus will depart from the high school at 2:45.

The After Prom Party committee is having their last fundraiser of the year on February 8th at the Menno double-header in Wakonda. We will need 8 gallons of chicken noodle soup and 5 gallons of chili donated. Also, we need baskets donated for a silent auction to make this fundraiser a hit. We will be in charge of the concessions that day as well, we need about 16 people to run the concessions. The first game starts at 2:00, so we need our first helpers to arrive at 1:30.

Please let me(605-661-9799), Brandy, or Melissa know where you can help or if you can donate soup or baskets.

Thank you!
Heather Logue

All state chorus and orchestra concert tonight at 7:00 on South Dakota Public Broadcasting. They have worked so hard and have created some amazing music. Their performance is powerful. Thank you for everything and all your hard work for the past four years! I can’t wait to see what you accomplish! Love you all! Thanks for being some great students to spend my birthday weekend with!

post_text:
The issue of vaping/Juuling has gained a lot of attention recently. Vaping nicotine nearly doubled among high school seniors from 11 percent in 2017 to 20.9 percent in 2018. More than 1 in 10 eighth graders (10.9 percent) say they vaped nicotine in the past year, and use is up significantly in virtually all vaping measures among eighth, 10th and 12th graders. These are—by far—the biggest one-year increases ever seen for any substance in the history of the NIDA Monitoring the Future survey.

Please take the time to keep yourself informed on the trends. Here is one of the best resource sites available:
https://www.cdc.gov/tobacco/basic_information/e-cigarettes/Quick-Facts-on-the-Risks-of-E-cigarettes-for-Kids-Teens-and-Young-Adults.html

One of the new trends that has surfaced in our area is called dabbing. For more information on dabbing see the link below.
https://www.centeronaddiction.org/the-buzz-blog/dabbing-what-you-need-know-about-latest-marijuana-craze

post_text:
Good Tuesday evening!

It is hard to believe that the school year is almost at an end. Students at the junior high and high school will be taking semester tests on Wednesday and Friday this week. On Thursday we will have a large number of students competing in the conference track meet, the other students will spend the morning reviewing for their upcoming semester tests. Thursday afternoon we have several fun activities planned for students to pick from.

If your student(s) has earned a semester test exemption they may be excused from attending that testing session. Please call the school office at 605-263-3311 to excuse your student(s) if this option will be exercised.

On Friday, May 17th school will be dismissed at 1:30 for the JH and HS students, and at 1:45 for the elementary students. Prior to departing for the school year, students need to make sure their lockers are cleaned out, their laptops are turned in, and any fees or fines are paid.

*** Elementary Track and Field Day ***
Due to the cold and wet conditions at the track in Irene, we will not be having our traditional track and field day today. Wet conditions in Wakonda are also making it difficult for us to do outdoor activities. Therefore, we will be doing an indoor fun day this afternoon in the big gym in Wakonda. Students will participate in Scooter races, Standing Long Jump, Potato Race, Lightning, Team Hula, Relays, and an Obstacle Course. No ribbons will be awarded for this fun day. Events will still start at 12:30 p.m. Parents are more than welcome to come and watch!

post_text:
All three of the counties served by the Irene-Wakonda School District have issued travel bans on their gravel roads for our buses and all other non-essential travel.

Beginning Monday, April 8th, buses will be running on paved roads only and will continue to do so until the travel bans are lifted. Bus drivers will be contacting families regarding an alternative location for picking up and dropping off students.

We appreciate your cooperation and understanding in this matter and look forward to returning to the normal bus routes as soon as possible.

John Peterson, Glenridge Golf Course board member, asked me to share this wonderful opportunity with all of you.

Glenridge Golf Course in Irene is offering free junior golf memberships this year to all children in the surrounding area, ages 6-18 (including 2019 graduating seniors). Lessons will also be available starting in June. There are also other programs available to enroll in for discounted junior golf rates at courses around this area and across the nation.

Please contact John Peterson at (605) 660-5821 to sign up or for more information.

Please consider taking advantage of this opportunity.

post_text:
Trey King was selected as one of the All-American Football Players from South Dakota.

Each of the 7 classes of SD football voted for an All-American in their respective class during a meeting of the SDFBCA last fall. Trey King was selected as the 9AA representative. At a later date, the SDFBCA selected two of the seven to be the All-American representavitves from SD. The other 5 players would be listed as Honorable Mentions. This years All-Americans were Trey King & Tupak Kpeayeh. This is a first time a player from Irene-Wakonda has been selected for this prestigious honor.

Brent Mutchelknaus(Irene and Irene-Wakonda) and O.C. Heitman(Wakonda) will also be inducted into the Hall of Fame for the SDFBCA.
